('1002610', 1002610, 'Proposal', 'legacy coil replacement', '3490 Benton Street, Santa Clara', 'Santa Clara', 'Other', 2987.0, '2026-01-14', 'EVAPORATOR COIL ISSUE:

· After trouble-shooting the Evaporator Coil on the HVAC System, the following was determined:

· The evaporator coil has a large amount of dust and lint that has attached to it, and it is restricting the airflow · If the coil is removed from the system and washed and then reinstalled, it is not guaranteed that it will work due to the internal components inside the evaporator coil being very fragile and if there is any type of disturbance, it would create a leak, which would then result in the refrigerant leaking out · The cost of cleaning the coil would still require us to disassemble the system to pull the coil out and then reinstall it, therefore the labor cost for installing a new coil is about the same

· Due to the existing Evaporator Coil not being guaranteed to work after washing and reinstalling, we are recommending installing a New Evaporator Coil.

· Recover the existing R-410A Refrigerant from the system · Cut the line-set and remove the condensate drain from the existing evaporator coil · Disassemble and remove the existing evaporator coil from the supply plenum and furnace · Install a New Multi-Position Evaporator Coil onto the system · Make all necessary modification to the supply plenum to fit the new evaporator coil · Connect the line-set to the new evaporator coil · Connect the condensate drain to the new coil · Charge the system with R-410A Refrigerant · Ensure that the New Evaporator Coil is properly functioning', 'historical'),
